      <h3>About Gift Administration</h3> 
      <p>The mission of the UC Riverside Office of Gift Administration is to serve campus departments, the development staff and the University of California Office of the President (UCOP) as the delegated authority to accept, record, and receipt all charitable contributions to UC Riverside and the UC Riverside Foundation.</p> 
      <p>We record and receipt all gifts and pledges to the University, including checks, cash, credit cards, gifts of securities and gifts-in-kind. We ensure compliance with IRS regulations, Governmental Accounting Standards Board (GASB) accounting standards, and Council for Advancement and Support of Education (CASE) counting standards for all gifts to the University. Gift Administration is also responsible for ensuring the integrity of gift data recorded and stored in its donor database for the purpose of donor, departmental, and institutional reporting.</p> 
      <h4 class="section2">Tools &amp; Resources</h4> 
      <h5>Matching Gifts</h5> 
      <p><a href="/matching.html">Information on corporate matching gifts</a></p> 
      <h5>Gift Acceptance Form</h5> 
      <p>The standard UCR Gift/Private Grant Acceptance Form to be used with all donations.<br><a href="/pdf/giftacceptanceform.pdf">Download as a PDF.</a><br><a href="/word_excel/gift_acceptance_form.xls">Download as an Excel file.</a></p> 
      <h5>Payroll Deduction Form</h5> 
      <p>Form that allows you to support the UC Riverside Foundation through direct payroll deduction.<br><a href="/pdf/payrolldeduct.pdf">Download as a PDF.</a><br><a href="/word_excel/payrolldeduct.doc">Download as a Microsoft Word file.</a></p> 
      <h5>UCR Foundation Pledge/Donation Form</h5> 
      <p>Form to mail your pledge or gift to the UCR Foundation.<br><a href="/pdf/pledgeform2013.pdf">Download as a PDF.</a></p> 
